==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clich
<hw>Cli`ch⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>clich⟦eacute⟧</ets>, from <ets>clicher</ets> to stereotype.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A stereotype plate or any similar reproduction of
ornament, or lettering, in relief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a trite or obvious remark.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> platitude, banality, commonplace, bromide.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Clich⟦eacute⟧ casting</b></col>, <cd>a mode of obtaining
an impression from a die or woodcut, or the like, by striking it
suddenly upon metal which has been fused and is just becoming solid;
also, the casting so obtained.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cliched</ent>⟦br⟧
